Write a uniqueElement function that takes a non-empty arr array and value as arguments and returns true if the element with value is unique 
(that is it occurs only once in the array) and false otherwise.

Example:

uniqueElement ([10, 3, 4, 3, 5], 3) must return false;
uniqueElement ([10, 11, 12, 13], 11) must return true;
uniqueElement ([10, 12, 12, 12], 10) must return true;
uniqueElement ([5, 4, 4, 4, 3], 4) must return false.

Solution:

function uniqueElement(arr, value){
  return arr.indexOf(value) === arr.lastIndexOf(value);
}
